          "bespoke_eyebrow": "Made to Order",
          "bespoke_title": "Your vision, perfectly made",
          "bespoke_body": "<p><strong>Bespoke Bedding</strong></p><p><em>Made for the bed you actually sleep in.</em></p><p>Mass-produced bedding is built for an average that doesn't exist. Soie & Forme bedding is made the other way around — to your measurements, in your colors, finished by hand.</p><p><strong>Sheets, fitted and flat</strong></p><p>Cut to the dimensions of your mattress, not a standard size. Tell us the depth, the length, the width — including that extra inch for the topper, if you have one — and we'll cut accordingly. Flat sheets are sized with the drape you want, whether that's tucked-and-tight or generous and loose.</p><p><strong>Duvet and blanket covers</strong></p><p>Built to fit your insert, not the other way around. Choose your closure — hidden buttons in matching silk, mother-of-pearl, or a clean envelope fold. Internal corner ties keep everything in place.</p><p><strong>Pillow cases</strong></p><p>Standard, king, euro, boudoir, or a size we draft from your measurements. Choose envelope, hidden zip, or a flanged edge. Each case is finished to match the rest of the set, or styled as a single accent.</p><p><strong>The palette</strong></p><p>Our house colors begin where ink wash ends — bone, cream, mist, smoke, ash, deep olive, charred green, ink black. Each can be specified for any piece in your set.</p><p>For something outside the house palette, we offer custom dyeing on natural silk and fibre. Send us a reference — a photograph, a swatch, a memory of a color — and we'll match it as closely as the dye will allow. Natural fibre takes color the way it wants to, and we honor that; each piece carries the small variations of something made by hand.</p><p><strong>Hand-finished details</strong></p><p>Every bespoke piece is finished by hand. Choose from:</p><p>— <em>French seams</em> on all interior edges, so nothing rough touches skin<br/>— <em>Hand-rolled hems</em> on flat sheets and pillow shams<br/>— <em>Embroidery</em> in matching or contrasting thread — a monogram, a single character, a small motif drawn from your reference<br/>— <em>Piped or flanged edges</em> in a complementary tone from the palette<br/>— <em>Hemstitching</em> or <em>ladder stitch</em> along the top hem of flat sheets and pillowcases</p><p><strong>How it works</strong></p><p>Send us your measurements and your palette. We'll confirm the specification, share a small fibre and color sample for approval, and begin. Bespoke sets are made to order; lead time is typically four to six weeks.</p><p>Each set arrives wrapped in unbleached cotton, with care instructions and a small note of what was made, by whom, and on what day.</p>",
